Insurance Charges Prediction¶

Problem - 2 Medical Analysis 1. Understand the Data 2. Do proper Diagonistics of the Data 3. Prepare reporg in Tableau based on the Inisghts gather from the data 4. Perform EDA on the dataset 5. Build the Model to accurately predict the charges 6. Show proper model diagonistics for validations. 7. Share the Html file on mail. 8. Upload it in the Github #################################################### Columns age: age of primary beneficiary sex: insurance contractor gender, female, male bmi: Body mass index, providing an understanding of body, weights that are relatively high or low relative to height, objective index of body weight (kg / m ^ 2) using the ratio of height to weight, ideally 18.5 to 24.9 children: Number of children covered by health insurance / Number of dependents smoker: Smoking region: the beneficiary's residential area in the US, northeast, southeast, southwest, northwest. charges: Individual medical costs billed by health insurance ############## Objective ############# Can you accurately predict insurance costs?

Tableau Link: https://public.tableau.com/views/InsuranceCharges_16849470164730/InsuranceCharges?:language=en-US&publish=yes&:display_count=n&:origin=viz_share_link

In [36]:
def treat_outliers(data):
    q3 = np.percentile(data,75)
    q1 = np.percentile(data,25)
    iqr = q3 - q1
    upper = q3 + (1.5 * iqr)
    lower = q1 - (1.5 * iqr)
    for i in range(0,len(data)):
        if data[i] > upper:
            data[i] = upper
        elif data[i] < lower:
            data[i] = lower
    return data

def predict_charges():
    age = int(input("Enter your age: "))
    sex = int(input("Enter your sex(0 - Male,1-Female):"))
    bmi = float(input("Enter Your BMI: "))
    smoker = int(input("Enter yes/ no (1 / 0):"))
    age_coef,sex_coef,bmi_coef,smoker_coef = ridge_model.coef_.flatten()
    intercept = ridge_model.coef_[0][0]
    charges = (age*age_coef)+(sex*sex_coef)+(bmi*bmi_coef)+(smoker*smoker_coef) + intercept
    print("Insurance Charges is....",charges)
